        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 2:38AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 236 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Moore, or 14 miles west of Lewistown, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lewistown, Hobson, Moore, Danvers, Suffolk, Forestgrove, Moccasin,
Giltedge, Glengarry, Heath, Hilger, and Christina.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
